## Important Constraints
- Service Worker CANNOT use OPFS SyncAccessHandle (only available in dedicated Workers)
- Service Worker CAN use IndexedDB for sync queue persistence
- WASM binary caching is the highest-impact optimization (can be 2-8 MiB)
- Background Sync API has limited browser support (Chrome only as of 2026)
- Must handle SW updates carefully to avoid stale WASM versions

## Acceptance Criteria
1. Service Worker precaches WASM binary and critical JS assets on install
2. Cache-first strategy for WASM (large, versioned binary)
3. Stale-while-revalidate for JS/CSS (frequent updates)
4. Network-first for HTML (always try to get latest)
5. App works fully offline after initial load
6. Background sync queues mutations when offline, replays when online
7. SW update flow: detect new version, prompt user, activate cleanly
8. Detailed console logging at every SW lifecycle event
9. Graceful degradation when SW is not supported
